  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled a relatively modest sum and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. While embezzlement is a significant breach of trust, a long prison sentence is disproportionate for this specific case given the absence of prior criminal history and the ongoing restitution efforts. Ignoring the external pressure from the courtroom spectator, a 6-month period of incarceration is sufficient to serve as a deterrent and acknowledge the severity of the financial crime without being overly punitive for a first-time, non-violent offender.",
